# peers — the fleet of hosts that share projects, for cross-host jumping.
# One short hostname (output of `hostname -s`) per line. Each host skips itself,
# so the SAME file works on every box. Requires passwordless SSH between them.
#
# install.sh copies this to `peers` (gitignored, per-host) on first install.
# With everything commented out, proj stays single-host. Uncomment your fleet:
#red
#blu
#fnix
#nixf
